equation
    connect(powertrain.controlBus,controlBus) annotation(Line(points = {{120,-20},{120,74},{40,74},{40,100}},color = {240,170,40},pattern = LinePattern.Dot));
    annotation(Documentation(info = "<html><p>This is a Sedan vehicle model using the&nbsp;<a href=\"modelica://CDC2023.Vehicles.Chassis.Kinematic\">Kinematic</a> chassis,&nbsp;<a href=\"modelica://CDC2023.Vehicles.Powertrains.InWheelDrive\">InWheelDrive</a>&nbsp;powertrain and&nbsp;<a href=\"modelica://VehicleDynamics.Vehicles.Brakes.None\">None</a>&nbsp;brakes.</p><p>The use of the&nbsp;<a href=\"modelica://VehicleDynamics.Vehicles.Brakes.None\">None</a>&nbsp;brakes&nbsp;results into the model using the motor torques from the powertrain (Set using inputs to the signalBus) for braking instead of the driver inputs from the brakePedalFlange. In the same way, the drive torque is set directly instead of using the acceleratorPedalFlange input using a driver model.</p><p>Since the powertrain and brakes components don't have any masses inside, the chassis component defines the mass and inertia of the vehicle.</p></html>"));
